<p>So the question remains: What cool things did you do in Software this year?</p>
<p>(Or I guess, what cool features did you see in software this year, if it was something from another team!)</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2025-05-19T15:43:40.775Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":35,"reads":566,"readers_count":565,"score":423.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":502028,"topic_slug":"what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year","display_username":"joemost","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":9}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":20003,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year/502028/1","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":9}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":9,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3629082,"name":"Roman A.","username":"RomanTechPlus","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/romantechplus/{size}/214929_2.png","created_at":"2025-05-19T16:30:46.053Z","cooked":"<ol>
<li>
<p>GTSAM: Beyond the standard 4 camera <span class="abbreviation">PV<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Photon Vision, an open source vision library for coprocessors"></template></span> based apriltag detection system we’ve run for a few years now, this year we began using a factor-graph based system to generate pose estimates using GTSAM on our Nvidia Jetson Orin Nano Super Coprocessor.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Depth Camera: We used a StereoLabs ZED 2i depth camera on our robot (with a fully CUDA accelerated back-end) for object detection, which allowed us to fully automate intakeing in ground during teleop by measuring the true 3d position of, and angle relative to our camera, for coral. This allowed us to make a “single click” automated pickup sequence that ensures we can pickup coral easily from any angle. With this we achieved nearly 60fps performance, even with a full FP32 model.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Heavy Teleop automation: We created automated scoring, climbing, and HP intake sequences which were able to dynamically navigate around obstacles. we also pretty much totally automated turning for our driver, with that automation behavior changing based on the game and robot state.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Custom Button Board: We build a custom button control board which allowed our operator to initiate scoring sequences for any reef position (from anywhere on the filed), control the climb, and automation override. Though this also came with the goal of giving our diver as much control as possible, so they still had access to “smart” scoring buttons on the back of their controller.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>Honorable Mentions: LEDs that were actually surprisingly useful, massively overcomplicated superstructure motion logic, and a 200 line class solely devoted to allowing multi button command binds without having to press them at the exact same time.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2025-05-19T16:40:19.160Z","reply_count":3,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":553,"readers_count":552,"score":335.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":502028,"topic_slug":"what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year","display_username":"Roman A.","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":12}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53160,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"5104 BreakerBots | Software and Additive Mfg. Lead"},"post_url":"/t/what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year/502028/2","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":12},{"id":"open_mouth","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":13,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3629122,"name":"Barkın Var","username":"barkinvar","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/barkinvar/{size}/171468_2.png","created_at":"2025-05-19T17:05:40.904Z","cooked":"<p>Do you have any video of object detection with the depth camera? I am really interested in the accuracy of it.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2025-05-19T17:05:40.904Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":475,"readers_count":474,"score":170.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":502028,"topic_slug":"what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year","display_username":"Barkın Var","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":53160,"username":"RomanTechPlus","name":"Roman A.","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/romantechplus/{size}/214929_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":5}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":50115,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"9483 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year/502028/3","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":5}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":5,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3629131,"name":"Tyler Veness","username":"calcmogul","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/calcmogul/{size}/128045_2.png","created_at":"2025-05-19T17:14:56.382Z","cooked":"<p>I saw some teams use Choreo for straight-line trajectories. It was massive overkill for this year’s game. <img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/images/emoji/google/slight_smile.png?v=12" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:" loading="lazy" width="20" height="20"></p>
<p>Speaking of overkill, my favorite WPILib 2025 snippet is <a href="https://github.wpilib.org/allwpilib/docs/release/java/edu/wpi/first/math/geometry/Ellipse2d.html#nearest(edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Translation2d)" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Ellipse2d.nearest()</a> because it uses a very big hammer to solve an easy-to-describe but <a href="https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/2785107/how-to-find-the-point-on-an-ellipse-that-is-closest-to-the-point-a-outside-of-th" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">annoying-to-solve</a> problem in a readable way. Here’s the C++ version we wrapped in JNI:</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="cpp"><code class="lang-cpp">Translation2d Ellipse2d::Nearest(const Translation2d&amp; point) const {
  // Check if already in ellipse
  if (Contains(point)) {
    return point;
  }

  // Rotate the point by the inverse of the ellipse's rotation
  auto rotPoint =
      point.RotateAround(m_center.Translation(), -m_center.Rotation());

  // Find nearest point
  {
    namespace slp = sleipnir;

    sleipnir::OptimizationProblem problem;

    // Point on ellipse
    auto x = problem.DecisionVariable();
    x.SetValue(rotPoint.X().value());
    auto y = problem.DecisionVariable();
    y.SetValue(rotPoint.Y().value());

    problem.Minimize(slp::pow(x - rotPoint.X().value(), 2) +
                     slp::pow(y - rotPoint.Y().value(), 2));

    // (x − x_c)²/a² + (y − y_c)²/b² = 1
    // b²(x − x_c)² + a²(y − y_c)² = a²b²
    double a2 = m_xSemiAxis.value() * m_xSemiAxis.value();
    double b2 = m_ySemiAxis.value() * m_ySemiAxis.value();
    problem.SubjectTo(b2 * slp::pow(x - m_center.X().value(), 2) +
                          a2 * slp::pow(y - m_center.Y().value(), 2) ==
                      a2 * b2);

    problem.Solve();

    rotPoint = frc::Translation2d{units::meter_t{x.Value()},
                                  units::meter_t{y.Value()}};
  }

  // Undo rotation
  return rotPoint.RotateAround(m_center.Translation(), m_center.Rotation());
}
</code></pre>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2025-05-19T17:14:56.382Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":471,"readers_count":470,"score":229.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":502028,"topic_slug":"what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year","display_username":"Tyler Veness","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/2785107/how-to-find-the-point-on-an-ellipse-that-is-closest-to-the-point-a-outside-of-th","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":43},{"url":"https://github.wpilib.org/allwpilib/docs/release/java/edu/wpi/first/math/geometry/Ellipse2d.html#nearest(edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Translation2d)","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Ellipse2d (WPILib API 2025.3.2)","clicks":12}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":8}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":16846,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"WPILib controls | Choreo optimizer backend"},"post_url":"/t/what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year/502028/4","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":8}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":8,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3629155,"name":"Amicus1","username":"Amicus1","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/a9adbd/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-05-19T17:37:23.392Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="calcmogul" data-po