<p>What about the students?</p>","post_number":18,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2025-05-27T15:43:27.251Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":16,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":159,"readers_count":158,"score":261.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":502028,"topic_slug":"what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year","display_username":"Eli Barnett","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":15}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":12381,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Robot apartments! invisible suburbs! skeleton treasuries!"},"post_url":"/t/what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year/502028/18","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":14},{"id":"point_up","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":15,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3636970,"name":"","username":"TheComputer314","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/thecomputer314/{size}/241453_2.png","created_at":"2025-05-27T16:11:07.296Z","cooked":"<p>I had a potential field pathfinder for autos/teleop autoalign which was a modification from a impl by <a class="mention" href="/u/amicus1">@Amicus1</a> and apparently A LOT of people copied my impl. It also won us IIC at <span class="abbreviation">MOSE<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Central Missouri"></template></span> so that was cool.</p>
<p>I had a fully modular auto system made that let me go to any reef location in any order, reliably. I just had to define which source to go to and which reef locations to go to, and the robot would score L4 coral there. I also had a similar system for algae autos, but we didn’t get to use it.</p>
<p>This was the first year we had a PhotonVision setup, and we had some suboptimal camera placements which caused issues, but it was otherwise flawless. It let us have incredibly reliable localization for the autoalign.</p>","post_number":19,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2025-05-27T16:11:07.296Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":162,"readers_count":161,"score":52.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":502028,"topic_slug":"what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62207,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"The one crazy dude on 167"},"post_url":"/t/what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year/502028/19","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3636979,"name":"","username":"glolichen07","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/glolichen07/{size}/258867_2.png","created_at":"2025-05-27T16:25:20.111Z","cooked":"<p>Personally I really liked using linear algebra for our reef alignment system. By changing the basis of the error vector (between the robot’s current position and the desired target for coral scoring) from standard <span class="math">(x,y)</span> coordinates into “depth” and “lateral” coordinates (facing directly out of the AprilTag, and perpendicular to it) and running a <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> controller on the depth and lateral errors, we could get the lateral movement to be faster than the depth and converge laterally first. Which means by the end of the align robot would pretty much only be moving forward.</p>
<p>The math isn’t that complicated but it’s great to apply some stuff we learned in math to real life!</p>
<p>If <span class="math">\theta</span> is the angle of the AprilTag then the “depth vector” controlling forward/backward movement would be <span class="math">\vec D=\begin{bmatrix}\cos\theta \\\sin\theta \end{bmatrix}</span> and the “lateral vector” for left/right would be <span class="math">\vec L=\begin{bmatrix}-\sin\theta\\\cos\theta\end{bmatrix}</span> so <span class="math">\vec{L} \cdot \vec{D}=0</span> so they are perpendicular. Then if we have the error vector <span class="math">E=\begin{bmatrix}a\\b\end{bmatrix}</span> (which we obtain with [Limelight MegaTag2 estimated pose] - [desired pose]) we would need to find <span class="math">d,l</span> such that <span class="math">d\vec D+l\vec L=E</span>.</p>
<p>Which would be: <span class="math">d\begin{bmatrix}\cos\theta \\ \sin\theta\end{bmatrix}+l\begin{bmatrix}-\sin\theta \\ \cos\theta\end{bmatrix}=\begin{bmatrix} a \\ b \end{bmatrix}</span></p>
<p>Which is equivalent to <span class="math">\begin{bmatrix}\cos\theta &amp; -\sin\theta \\ \sin\theta &amp; \cos\theta\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix} d \\ l \end{bmatrix}=\begin{bmatrix}a \\ b \end{bmatrix}</span>.</p>
<p>Multiplying by the inverse on the left gives <span class="math">\begin{bmatrix} d \\ l \end{bmatrix}=\begin{bmatrix}\cos\theta &amp; -\sin\theta \\ \sin\theta &amp; \cos\theta\end{bmatrix}^{-1}\begin{bmatrix} a \\ b \end{bmatrix}</span> <span class="math">=\frac{1}{\cos^2\theta+\sin^2\theta}\begin{bmatrix}\cos\theta &amp; \sin\theta \\ -\sin\theta &amp; \cos\theta\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix} a \\ b \end{bmatrix}</span> <span class="math">=\begin{bmatrix} a\cos \theta+b\sin\theta \\ -a\sin\theta+b\cos\theta \end{bmatrix}</span>.</p>
<p>Then we run the <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> controller on <span class="math">d</span> and <span class="math">l</span> individually with different <span class="math">K_p</span> values.</p>","post_number":20,"post_type":1,"posts_count":24,"updated_at":"2025-05-27T16:35:47.315Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":158,"readers_count":157,"score":166.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":502028,"topic_slug":"what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/how-did-your-team-do-auto-alignment-this-year/503341/6","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"How did your team do auto alignment this year?","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":7}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":63443,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"FRC 5895"},"post_url":"/t/what-cool-things-did-you-do-in-software-this-year/502028/20","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":6},{"id":"100","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":7,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null}],"stream":[3629026,3629082,3629122,3629131,3629155,3629158,3629163,3630183,3630196,3630384,3630397,3631210,3631348,3631762,3636861,3636874,3636902,3636940,3636970,3636979,3637001,3637004,3637043,3637169]},"ti